Commercial and industrial demand for transportation services arises from
delivery of goods (freight) via supply chains
as shown in Figure~\ref{fig:tonnekm_by_mode}.
Consumer demand for freight transport services arises from increased online shopping
in recent years.
One of the most important aspects of freight transportation is the 
``last mile problem''~\cite{World-Economic-Forum:2020wf}, 
the expensive and time-intensive transport of goods
on the last leg of their journey to 
consumers and businesses.
Typically, the last leg involves moving goods from a distribution center
to the purchaser.
The rise of e-commerce has caused unparalleled growth in last-mile transport
in recent years. 
The result is rising energy consumption and
CO$_2$ emissions from commercial last-mile deliveries.


